<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14180] cassandra.spec needs to require ant-junit</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14180</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I tried rebuilding cassandra-3.11.1-1.src.rpm on a Centos 7 host which had ant installed, but not the &quot;ant-junit&quot; package; that failed with a somewhat cryptic error message. It turnout out I needed to have the &quot;ant-junit&quot; package installed, as well. So for the cassandra.spec file, I suggest that the following line be added just below the existing BuildRequires line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;BuildRequires: ant-junit &amp;gt;= 1.9&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13132515">CASSANDRA-14180</key>
